    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20/134</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Iranian Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schayesteh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3382</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-20">March 20,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister of Iran presents his compliments to His Excellency the Secretary of
                    State and has the honor to inform him that the Iranian Government intends to
                    engage a high ranking American officer to take charge of the entire finance and
                    army supply divisions of the Iranian War Department. This office is called
                    “Intendant General,” which, I believe, corresponds in the United States to
                    General Service of Supply.</p>
                <p>The Minister would appreciate it very much if the Secretary of State would
                    consent to give him the name of a suitable officer to be engaged by the Iranian
                    Government.</p>
            </div>
